author: Inside Edition
description: Police are desperately looking for a woman who they say was violently abducted. Her suspected assailant put her in a tight bear hug and dragged her off in the dark. It happened in Wichita, Kansas. Police say it was 2 a.m. Sunday when a surveillance camera recorded the abduction. Police took the tape and reduced the background noise, hoping someone will recognize her voice when she screams. Inside Edition showed the video to self-defense expert Matan Gavish.
title: Kansas Woman's Violent Abduction Caught On Surveillance Camera: Cops

author: Inside Edition
description: Donna Adelson learned her fate following her conviction for having her son-in-law gunned down in his driveway. The 75-year-old insists she's innocent and was not the mastermind behind the assassination of Daniel Markel. A month ago, a jury found Adelson guilty of arranging the shooting death of Markel, so that her daughter, Wendi, and two grandchildren could move closer to her. Adelson was sentenced to life without parole. She says she will appeal her conviction.
title: 'Monster-In-Law' Donna Adelson Sentenced To Life Without Parole

author: Inside Edition
description: The latest issue of Time Magazine hails President Donald Trump for brokering the Gaza ceasefire. But the picture may be the "worst of all time," Trump said on Truth Social. The photo was taken last week outside the White House as the president was heading to the Naval Academy. While praising the coverage as a "good story," Trump could not get past the image. Trump is back in Washington Tuesday after his trip to the Middle East.
title: President Trump Says His Time Magazine Cover Photo Is 'Super Bad'

author: Inside Edition
description: Ellen Greenberg was stabbed more than 20 times, yet her death was ruled a suicide. After a 13-year-long struggle, her parents managed to get the case reopened. But her death has once again been ruled a suicide Tuesday, and the case is officially closed. A medical examiner says many of Greenberg's injuries are "hesitation wounds" and that "Ellen would be capable of inflicting these wounds herself." Inside Edition spoke to the family's attorney, who says the latest findings make no sense.
title: Ellen Greenberg's Stabbing Death Once Again Ruled A Suicide

author: Inside Edition
description: Neo-soul singer D'Angelo has died. TMZ reports the artist passed away in New York City after a lengthy and private battle with pancreatic cancer. His real name was Michael Eugene Archer, and he is credited with ushering in a new era of soul music in the late 90s and early 2000s. He was recognized with four Grammys and numerous other accolades. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Neo-Soul Singer D'Angelo Dies At 51

title: Hero Nurse Saves Buffalo Bills Fan #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Sarah and Keith Hurley are now warning of the dangers of old grenades after their 12-year-old son Asher was tragically killed when a WWII grenade the family thought was an inactive dummy exploded in his bedroom. Explosives experts tell INSIDE EDITION that old grenades can be ticking time bombs and should be turned over to the authorities whenever found. The Hurley’s have created a music scholarship in Asher’s honor. For more information, click here: https://bit.ly/4hiFGGw
title: Parents Warn Of The Dangers Of Old War Grenades

title: Former Rock Star Ian Watkins Killed In Prison #shorts
